<br>
It's good to be the wiz.<br>
<br>
Awlin (erudite wiz) is now 51, with 17 days played and about 14k in equipment, int maxed, and resists mostly over 90.  Aidal (high elf cleric) is now 57, with over 80 days played, close to 30k in equipment, about half of which is nodrop (no resale :-(), wis about 110 with resists under 40 or 70+ resists with wis 170.<br>
<br>
Awlin made more cash at level 28 than Aidal makes at 57.  Awlin made her first 1kpp in the early 30's.  Aidal made his first 1kpp at 47 and spent it on his level 44 spell.<br>
<br>
Awlin spends about 95% of her time hunting, (the rest is kei hunting, porting, chasing spells).  Aidal spends about 40% of his time hunting, about 40% of his time lfg, and about 20% getting from one place to another.<br>
<br>
Awlin is welcome in most cities.  Her first max pos faction was othmir.  At 51, she has no max negs.  Aidal is KOS in about half the cities in the world, including his home town.  His first max pos faction was iksar warrior guild, though he had about 14 max neg before that.<br>
<br>
Awlin lives on kei.  Gate to nexus, do a few tl's, buy a hit of kei, gate back to camp.  Aidal gets kei on most raids, (can't get to it or afford it the rest of the time).<br>
<br>
From about 39-51, Awlin levelled in about 3-5hrs, (roughly one play session, potential for 2 levels in a long day).  In those same levels, Aidal spent anywhere from 2-20hrs lfg, which led to weeks per level, even playing 10-14hrs/day.<br>
<br>
Awlin can still quad blue, single white or yellow.  Aidal, with the recent hammer upgrade, can now kill green and even some not-undead blue.<br>
<br>
Aidal is in demand for raids, that's true.  Raids can't happen without sufficient clerics.  But he's in a gross surplus when it comes to exp and can't exp usefully on his own.  People get very upset if he declines to rez or raid, though each requires hours of commitment and usually results in zero gain for Aidal.  Awlin has little trouble finding raids, people thank her graciously for ports (and pay).<br>
<br>
All in all, between the prevalence of kei, focus items, the bazaar, good hunt locations, cash from ports, the ability to solo (quite well), good group dps and utility, it is my opinion that it has never been a better time to be a wiz.<br>
